    <section id="about" class="about">
        <h2>About the majesty of Indian temples</h2>
        <p>Indian temples are not merely architectural marvels; they are profound centers of spiritual energy, cultural heritage, and historical significance. These temples epitomize the artistic excellence, deep devotion, and rich history unique to their respective regions. Each temple tells a story of faith, architectural grandeur, and cultural tradition, reflecting the soul of India's diverse spiritual landscape. This page is dedicated to showcasing some of the most renowned temples across India, celebrating their majestic beauty, intricate designs, and the timeless legends they embody. From the snow-capped Kedarnath in the Himalayas to the grand Ram Mandir in Ayodhya, each temple offers a glimpse into India's rich spiritual tapestry. Explore the majestic temples, learn about their architectural intricacies, spiritual significance, and the vibrant festivals celebrated. Immerse yourself in the fascinating history and spirituality that make these temples true treasures of India's cultural heritage.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="temples" class="featured-temples">
        <h2>Featured Temples</h2>
        <div class="temple-cards">
            <div class="temple-card">
                <img src="https://www.tourmyindia.com/blog//wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Badrinath-Temple-1.jpg" alt="Badrinath">
                <h3>Badrinath Temple</h3>
                <p>Location: Uttarakhand</p>
                <p>Situated close to the Alaknanda River, the abode of Lord Badrinath is located in the Chamoli district of Uttarakhand. This holy shrine of Lord Vishnu is one of the Char Dhams of Hindu religion</p>
                <a href="#">Read More ➡</a>
            </div>
            <div class="temple-card">
                <img src="https://www.tourmyindia.com/blog//wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Sun-Temple-Konark-Odisha.jpg" alt="Ram Mandir">
                <h3>Sun Temple</h3>
                <p>Location: Orrisa</p>
                <p>At this marvel of architecture is dedicated to Indian God of Sun, Surya. The temple has been built in the shape of his chariot which is drawn by seven horses.</p>
                <a href="#">Read More ➡</a>
            </div>
            <div class="temple-card">
                <img src="https://www.tourmyindia.com/blog//wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Somnath-Temple.jpg" alt="Temple 3">
                <h3>Somnath Temple</h3>
                <p>Location: Gujarat</p>
                <p>Somnath Temple is one of the oldest pilgrimage centres in India and finds mention in the ancient books of Shiv Puran, Skanda Purana and Shreemad Bhagvat Gita. Soma refers to 'Moon God', thus Somnath means 'Protector of the Moon God'.</p>
                <a href="#">Read More ➡</a>
            </div>
            <div class="temple-card">
                <img src="https://www.tourmyindia.com/blog//wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Rameshwaram-Temple.jpg" alt="Temple 4">
                <h3>Ramanathaswamy Temple</h3>
                <p>Location: Tamil Nadu</p>
                <p>Rameswaram is a small island town in Tamil Nadu known for being one of the pious Char Dhams of the Hindus. As per the legend, Lord Rama with his wife Sita landed on the shore of this island after defeating the demon king, Ravana who was a brahmin.</p>
                <a href="#">Read More ➡</a>
            </div>
        </div>
